<TITLE> Economist Omar H Chy dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com)Omar Haider Chowdhury, one of Bangladesh's top economists, died in Dhaka Friday night, his family said. He was 65. Chowdhury, who had retired as research director from Bangladesh's premier social science research institution BIDS late last year, had been hospitalised for two weeks before his death at 10:15pm at a city hospital. His Namaz-e-Janaza will be held at the Road 7 Dhanmondi mosque after Zohr prayers on Saturday, Osman Kaiser Chowdhury, one of his younger brothers, told bdnews24.com. Dr Chowdhury left behind three daughters and wife. The eldest of three brothers, he had long been regarded as Bangladesh's top fiscal policy specialist and was educated in Dhaka, Manchester and London. Osman Kaiser Chowhury is Director, Group Finance and Corporate Affairs at the Beximco Group, and the youngest brother, Akku Chowhdury, is chief executive of Liberation War Museum. Omar Haider Chowdhury worked as a consultant to World Bank, ADB, FAO, ESCAP and APDC and advised the government on various issues. As BIDS director, he headed the general economics division and led numerous research and studies. 
